== Spam-Regex still problematic ==

Cannot edit [[GoodFonts]]. Ostensibly because of all the numbers :\
I visit EmacsWiki maybe once a year: my additions are in [[NealePickett]] under "Variable Pitch", if someone would like to paste it in after the page can be edited. -- [[NealePickett]] 2016-11-01

[new]
I looked at the ##spammer.log## file linked to from the WikiSpam page, listing the current "foiled" attempts at spamming the wiki. It lists time stamp, IP number, page name, and a message mentioning the regular expression triggered and the text matched. A quick review for the last month shows that all the "foiled" edits were probably legitimate edit attempts! Clearly, the false positives are a problem and I have therefore commented the [[BannedRegexps|problematic regular expressions]]. I hope this resolves the isse. :) -- Alex Schroeder

== Spam-regex too restrictive ==

I'm unable to edit the [[CategoryTemplates]] page, because it contains a "phone-number" in one of it's links to a template package.

[new]
I changed the code such that the regular expressions on BannedRegexps no longer apply to URLs because URLs have their own set of (more restrictive) regular expressions on BannedContent. -- [[Alex Schroeder]]

